mes Broughton. His brother, Jack Stauffacher, is a well-known printer and typeface creator. On December 18, 2013, Notes on the Port of St. Francis was selected for the Library of Congress's National Film Registry.\nFrom November 1948 until his death at age 38 from a brain tumor, Stauffacher was married to graphic artist Barbara Stauffacher Solomon.\nStauffacher's short film Zigzag was preserved by the Academy Film Archive in 2013.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T14:52:12.057849+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 3994, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Stauffacher"}], "uuid": "e35aee0f-6af4-4b23-82a4-e6ac5cd9edd0", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "19175", "external_references": [{"id": 26521, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q5489755"}, {"id": 28464, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "57386704"}, {"id": 28465, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no2003026076"}, {"id": 28466, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no2003026076"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-06T23:06:51.867409+11:00"}]}